<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Firmware Installation API</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background-color: #f4f4f9;
        color: #333;
        text-align: center;
      }
      header {
        background-color: #4caf50;
        color: white;
        padding: 20px 0;
      }
      h1 {
        margin: 0;
      }
      p {
        margin: 10px 0;
      }
      ul {
        list-style: none;
        padding: 0;
      }
      li {
        margin: 5px 0;
      }
      .container {
        padding: 20px;
      }
      .button {
        display: inline-block;
        margin-top: 20px;
        padding: 10px 20px;
        background-color: #4caf50;
        color: white;
        text-decoration: none;
        border-radius: 5px;
        font-size: 16px;
      }
      .button:hover {
        background-color: #45a049;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header>
      <h1>Welcome to the Firmware Installation API</h1>
    </header>
    <div class="container">
      <p>Use the following endpoints:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>POST</strong> /api/firmware-installation - Record new firmware
          installation
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>GET</strong> /api/firmware-installation/:system_uid - Get
          installation history for a UID
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>POST</strong> /api/deprecate-uid - Deprecate previous UID
          records
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div
        style="
          background: #e3f2fd;
          padding: 15px;
          border-radius: 5px;
          margin: 20px 0;
          text-align: left;
        "
      >
        <h3 style="color: #1976d2; margin-top: 0">API Information</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>New Feature:</strong> The deprecate UID endpoint automatically
          marks previous firmware records as deprecated when a new UID is
          installed on the same device. This maintains historical data while
          clearly indicating which records are currently active.
        </p>
        <p><strong>Status Meanings:</strong></p>
        <ul style="text-align: left">
          <li>
            <strong>Active:</strong> Current, verified firmware installation
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Deprecated:</strong> Previous UID that has been replaced
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <a href="/view-installations" class="button">View Installations</a>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
